<paragraph blockId="25.[151,1436,1029,1341]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,392,1029,1054]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" reason="1">Subgenus diagnosis.</emphasis>
Body length: 
<quantity box="[556,680,1029,1053]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2" metricValueMax="1.3" metricValueMin="1.1" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" unit="mm" value="12.0" valueMax="13.0" valueMin="11.0">11–13 mm</quantity>
. Male frontal calli very close to each other in the middle of frons, and only slightly raised over the head (
<figureCitation box="[583,670,1065,1089]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="16.[151,250,897,920]" captionTargetBox="[157,1421,297,866]" captionTargetId="figure-587@16.[151,1436,279,876]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 5. Male head, dorsal view: A, C. schreberi; B, C. scovitzi; C, C. vahli; D, C. adamovichiana; E, C. kunzei; F, C. schaefferi. Scale bar = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5286907" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5286907/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Fig. 5C</figureCitation>
). Male antennae modified: antennomere I dorsally expanded to form a high and narrow keel and with a pointed and curved expansion on external side; II simple, small and subcylindrical; III swollen, with a deep depression associated with a pointed expansion on external side; IV–V enlarged, flattened and very close to each other; VI distinctly swollen; VII–VIII slightly swollen and cup-like, VIII larger than VII; IX distinctly swollen and roughly circular. Male maxillary palpi distinctly modified: palpomere I slender, about 3 times as long as wide; II–III enlarged, flattened and curved; IV flattened, slender and subrectangular, about twice as long as wide. Male protibiae with a deep incision on external side and a weak dorsal keel; apically enlarged and swollen.
</paragraph>
